      <name>Grafana Privilege Escalation Vulnerability (GHSA-ff5c-938w-8c9q)</name>
      <modification_time>2026-01-26T08:53:46Z</modification_time>
      <comment />
      <creation_time>2026-01-26T08:53:46Z</creation_time>
      <host>127.0.0.1<asset asset_id="0691ec89-cd2a-4671-b577-82fbc9631e33" /><hostname>host1.example.com</hostname></host>
      <port>3000/tcp</port>
      <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.148743">
        <type>nvt</type>
        <name>Grafana Privilege Escalation Vulnerability (GHSA-ff5c-938w-8c9q)</name>
        <family>Web application abuses</family>
        <cvss_base>6.6</cvss_base>
        <severities score="6.6">
          <severity type="cvss_base_v3">
            <origin>NVD</origin>
            <date>2022-09-22T14:11:00Z</date>
            <score>6.6</score>
            <value>CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H</value>
          </severity>
        </severities>
        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=Grafana is prone to a privilege escalation vulnerability.|insight=Grafana allows an escalation from Admin privileges to Server
  Admin when Auth proxy authentication is used.

  Auth proxy allows to authenticate a user by only providing the username (or email) in a
  X-WEBAUTH-USER HTTP header: the trust assumption is that a front proxy will take care of
  authentication and that Grafana server is publicly reachable only with this front proxy.

  Datasource proxy breaks this assumption:

  - it is possible to configure a fake datasource pointing to a localhost Grafana install with a
  X-WEBAUTH-USER HTTP header containing admin username.

  - This fake datasource can be called publicly via this proxying feature.|affected=Grafana prior to version 8.5.13, version 9.0.x through 9.0.8
  and 9.1.x through 9.1.5 if the Auth Proxy is used.|impact=|solution=Update to version 8.5.13, 9.0.9, 9.1.6 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 8.5.13, 9.0.9, 9.1.6 or later.</solution>
        <refs>
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2022-35957" />
          <ref type="url" id="https://github.com/grafana/grafana/security/advisories/GHSA-ff5c-938w-8c9q" />
          <ref type="cert-bund" id="WID-SEC-2022-1486" />
          <ref type="dfn-cert" id="DFN-CERT-2023-1430" />
